Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.92,0:00:04.32,Default,,0,0,0,,"Dad, don't marry Frau Gerlach,"
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.37,0:00:09.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Lotte was so sick worried about it, \Nshe actually fell ill.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.93,0:00:14.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Upon discovering that, Luise and mother rushed to Vienna.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.66,0:00:19.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Finally, the time had come \Nfor all the secrets to come to light.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.23,0:00:26.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Abrogating her pledge, Luise disclosed to father and mother \Nthe fact of twins having switched places. {tsuini is act. another "finally" and he said THREE fucking different "finally" in this recap alone}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.61,0:00:30.44,Default,,0,0,0,,And thus, right there, on Lotte's bedside,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.94,0:00:34.68,Default,,0,0,0,,at long last, the family of four had been reunited.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.20,0:00:40.26,Sign,,0,0,100,,{\c&HCAEFF0&\bord0\blur0.8\fs30}Episode 25 \N {\fs55} Love Reborn!? {よみがえった愛!?} \N\N\N\N\N\N {\fs23} \h Translation: Perevodildo | Timings: Sub-RoRo \h
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.49,0:00:49.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Lotte.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.00,0:00:52.44,Default,,0,0,0,,She is asleep already.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.64,0:00:56.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Doctor Strobl had arrived. {/came to see you? I think}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.24,0:00:57.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Please.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.34,0:00:58.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Are we looking better?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.61,0:01:01.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, the fever is nearly gone, it seems.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.51,0:01:03.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Splendid.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.10,0:01:06.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Told you, any extra check-up would be superfluous.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.08,0:01:09.52,Default,,0,0,0,,However, you shouldn't let your guard down.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.06,0:01:14.56,Default,,0,0,0,,It's best that tonight \Nyou stay closely by her side, just in case.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.56,0:01:17.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Right, I was also hoping I could stay here overnight. {no clue what she means, deepl: Yes, I would do the same for you. - why such a weird wording, I would assume she means "I was hoping I could stay in this house, but it only has one bed"}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:24.07,0:01:25.41,Default,,0,0,0,,It's probably better this way. {still not sure what's implied here, most likely is not enough beds, but maybe, just maybe he means "I can entrust this to you and leave myself"}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.61,0:01:32.86,Default,,0,0,0,,They are still such a long way \Nfrom defeating awkwardness... {not sure what she means, deepl: That's not an easy thing to work out.}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.49,0:01:50.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Tonight, I'm staying in my atelier.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.66,0:01:54.07,Default,,0,0,0,,This way, I won't get in the way \Nof you nursing the girl. {lit is "you'll also be able to ... without worrying about me" but why'd she worry about him? I think this is a continuation of previous implied dialogue and they still mean either not enough beds or they just feel awkward in each other's presence}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.80,0:01:56.54,Default,,0,0,0,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.87,0:02:00.94,Default,,0,0,0,,So...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.73,0:02:04.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I entrust Lotte to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.35,0:02:24.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Luise.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.06,0:02:29.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Somehow, I knew... you'd come.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.89,0:02:31.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Awake already?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.03,0:02:34.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, Lotte, what in the world happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.27,0:02:38.27,Default,,0,0,0,,A terrible thing. \NDad is engaged with Frau Gerlach.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.71,0:02:40.78,Default,,0,0,0,,No way!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.31,0:02:46.21,Default,,0,0,0,,When I learned of this, somehow, \NI was feeling worse and worse.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.78,0:02:50.18,Default,,0,0,0,,This is not happening!  \NAbsolutely not happening!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.36,0:02:52.59,Default,,0,0,0,,But what can we do?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.40,0:02:58.60,Default,,0,0,0,,You shouldn't be worried no more, Lotte.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.60,0:03:00.57,Default,,0,0,0,,After all, I'm here in Vienna with you!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.83,0:03:06.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Luise.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.57,0:03:09.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Cheer up. And get back on your feet soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.11,0:03:12.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Dad will not marry a woman...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.91,0:03:14.48,Default,,0,0,0,,...Other than our mom!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.47,0:03:16.55,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Never!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.14,0:04:12.90,Default,,0,0,0,,So? You like it?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.96,0:04:15.03,Default,,0,0,0,,I love it!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.03,0:04:16.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Great!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.67,0:04:21.27,Default,,0,0,0,,I made sure to put in plenty of fresh cream.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.27,0:04:22.91,Default,,0,0,0,,After all, it's your favorite.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.64,0:04:26.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Just like I remember it - \Nyour cooking is the best in the world!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.38,0:04:28.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.01,0:04:31.32,Default,,0,0,0,,But that doesn't mean \Nyou can just push the carrot to the side. {/collect in the corner}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.32,0:04:33.25,Default,,0,0,0,,You'd make me oh so happy if you eat it all!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.53,0:04:38.70,Default,,0,0,0,,But come on...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.18,0:04:43.66,Default,,0,0,0,,You even try to avoid it the same way I do! {unsure what she means by "the same as me, get angry; to get mad" most likely get angered by the same thing}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.43,0:04:50.07,Default,,0,0,0,,A scene of gaiety.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.12,0:04:52.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Doctor Strobl!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.72,0:04:53.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Welcome!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.05,0:04:56.48,Default,,0,0,0,,You can see, I'm full of life again!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.55,0:04:59.42,Default,,0,0,0,,The recovery is marvelous indeed.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.88,0:05:02.91,Default,,0,0,0,,It's because mom had applied \Nsome magical ointment! {/treatment/medicine}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.45,0:05:05.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Magical ointment?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.33,0:05:12.85,Default,,0,0,0,,In my long career, a good many lauded me \Nas a miracle physician, so I tried to live up to it, {noted doctor; excellent physician} {no clue what this second part of the sentence means}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.85,0:05:15.73,Default,,0,0,0,,but turns out, the world's first \Nmiracle physician had been you!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.61,0:05:21.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Lotte, do you want a refill?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.11,0:05:23.52,Default,,0,0,0,,I could eat a bit more.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.95,0:05:27.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, give me a moment to bring you another serving.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.52,0:05:33.02,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't know you're home.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.02,0:05:37.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah... It seems, there's no longer \Nany need to worry... About Lotte.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.43,0:05:40.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. She's out of woods now.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.02,0:05:41.69,Default,,0,0,0,,That's my daughter for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.17,0:05:43.43,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.66,0:05:46.43,Default,,0,0,0,,That's her mother for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.81,0:05:57.68,Default,,0,0,0,,My, that's nothing!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.58,0:05:59.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you serious?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.88,0:06:01.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Really impressive, Irene!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.78,0:06:04.74,Default,,0,0,0,,The world's greatest musician, Herr Palfy...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.74,0:06:06.21,Default,,0,0,0,,...Is engaged to you!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.64,0:06:08.86,Default,,0,0,0,,It was actually last week, when he proposed.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.86,0:06:14.06,Default,,0,0,0,,While doing it, he stared at me so earnestly, \NI could almost read it in his eyes: {fixedly (e.g. gaze, stare); intently (e.g. listen, think)}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.06,0:06:19.15,Default,,0,0,0,,"If you don't marry me, I'd rather go throw myself \Ninto the lake and die right there..."
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.15,0:06:21.73,Default,,0,0,0,,My, so romantic!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.73,0:06:23.13,Default,,0,0,0,,I really envy you.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.13,0:06:29.06,Default,,0,0,0,,In all of Vienna... No, in the whole world, \Nthe jealousy of women is probably directed at me right now. {/I've earned ...}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.98,0:06:35.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Frau Irene, we need to finish the preparations \Nfor the wedding ceremony. {advance arrangements; preparatory meeting; briefing session}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.24,0:06:39.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I told you before to not spare anything. \NMake it the grandest wedding ceremony the money can buy.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.98,0:06:41.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Right, understood.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.22,0:06:44.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Irene!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.42,0:06:47.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Father? What in the world had happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.84,0:06:49.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Need a word. Now.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.89,0:06:52.83,Default,,0,0,0,,What might it be? \NExcuse me for a minute, will you?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.92,0:06:58.86,Default,,0,0,0,,A word just came,\NHerr Palfy's wife is spotted in Vienna!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.30,0:07:03.54,Default,,0,0,0,,No, to be precise, his ex-wife.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.54,0:07:07.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Perhaps, it's the mother \Nof the impeding little beast? {nuisance; obstructive (person); troublesome (person)}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.54,0:07:09.75,Default,,0,0,0,,It seems, she's in Palfy's house right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.31,0:07:11.84,Default,,0,0,0,,What did you say?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.22,0:07:23.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Here you go, Doctor Strobl.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.43,0:07:24.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Right, thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.86,0:07:26.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Here, for you as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.43,0:07:27.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.40,0:07:33.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Boo!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.00,0:07:44.78,Default,,0,0,0,,My, Luise! But what about the other Fraulein Twin?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.88,0:07:53.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Good heavens...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.15,0:07:55.38,Default,,0,0,0,,My, how should we even...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.15,0:07:57.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Quite confounding indeed.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.29,0:08:00.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, can you tell which one is Lotte now?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.35,0:08:02.15,Default,,0,0,0,,And which one is Luise?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.15,0:08:03.49,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Try to guess!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.44,0:08:14.77,Default,,0,0,0,,The one on the left is Luise, probably, I think...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.77,0:08:17.07,Default,,0,0,0,,No, if I try to distinct by the voice...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.57,0:08:22.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, I don't know now!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.60,0:08:25.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Frau and Herr Master, please come to our rescue!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.22,0:08:33.85,Default,,0,0,0,,You're Luise, aren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.31,0:08:36.36,Default,,0,0,0,,And here is Lotte.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.73,0:08:45.07,Default,,0,0,0,,On Luise's cheeks, there's always this sensation \Nof a place under the sun, my cute little tomboy. {/cheeks smell of the sun}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.51,0:08:48.04,Default,,0,0,0,,You really are my mom!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.77,0:08:50.71,Default,,0,0,0,,I knew them after just one close look - {nozokikomu is "to look into; to peer in" so imnot sure what he means}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.71,0:08:55.52,Default,,0,0,0,,those glittering eyes, \Nalways full of tears when you feel lonely.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.22,0:08:58.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Dad, love you!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.85,0:09:01.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, this is highly impressive!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.29,0:09:02.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Right you are!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.43,0:09:07.83,Default,,0,0,0,,I can now return to being Luise.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.93,0:09:18.10,Default,,0,0,0,,From today on, meet the old, boyish Luise!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.27,0:09:22.38,Default,,0,0,0,,I can also now return to being the usual Lotte.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.38,0:09:25.28,Default,,0,0,0,,And then, play piano to my heart's content! {to one's heart's content; to one's complete satisfaction; as much as one likes; heartily; thoroughly; without restraint; to the full}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.82,0:09:28.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, let's listen to your piano together! {/I want to...}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.58,0:09:29.99,Default,,0,0,0,,In dad's atelier!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.47,0:09:31.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Mom!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.75,0:09:34.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I want you to hear it, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.63,0:09:39.19,Default,,0,0,0,,And dad is coming with us!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.83,0:09:42.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I may...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.30,0:09:47.29,Default,,0,0,0,,As long as you don't mind. {I hope they imply here "if you don't mind my company"}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.83,0:09:51.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Amazing!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.52,0:10:04.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Dad!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.65,0:10:06.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Mom, you hurry up, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.86,0:10:12.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, Palfy listening.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.33,0:10:14.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, it's you, Luise?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.13,0:10:17.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Good morning. This is Gerlach speaking.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.10,0:10:18.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Frau Gerlach?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.67,0:10:21.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Could you invite Herr Palfy to the phone?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.80,0:10:24.74,Default,,0,0,0,,I wanted to ask him \Nto meet with me sometime soon. {not sure what's implied by korekara here}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.40,0:10:26.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Meet with you?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.90,0:10:29.97,Default,,0,0,0,,That's very apropos! \NDad asked me to pass this to you:
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.97,0:10:32.24,Default,,0,0,0,,"Wait for me in front of the Opera House."
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.62,0:10:34.65,Default,,0,0,0,,In front of the Opera House?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.65,0:10:37.07,Default,,0,0,0,,If I may, a useful tip for you - {I hope she means this and not "there, he'll tell you something good"}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.07,0:10:42.59,Default,,0,0,0,,dad is every inch an artist, so he especially likes a woman \Nwho surprises him by doing things out of ordinary.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.12,0:10:45.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Things out of ordinary?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.06,0:10:50.76,Default,,0,0,0,,For instance, like if you'd wait for him there, \Nfrozen like a statue, under two umbrellas! {motionlessly (e.g. stand, wait); (be) still​} {not a clue what's sashite, gotta be "between (e.g. two people); face to face" but I still don't see what it means}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.76,0:10:52.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Under two umbrellas?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.66,0:10:54.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Right! Under two!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.40,0:10:59.47,Default,,0,0,0,,That's remarkably well thought out for a joke.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.47,0:11:03.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, if you think it's a joke, \Njust disregard it altogether.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.34,0:11:03.94,Default,,0,0,0,,See you!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.57,0:11:07.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you sure, Luise? \NThis is getting pretty far.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.59,0:11:11.42,Default,,0,0,0,,It's fine, fine! It'd be her own fault \Nfor not smelling a joke here. {/the other side still thinks it's a joke}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.42,0:11:13.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Why the wait, you two?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.91,0:11:15.92,Default,,0,0,0,,It's nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.92,0:11:17.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's go, Lotte.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.13,0:11:29.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Under two umbrellas?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.44,0:11:49.08,Default,,0,0,0,,I wonder if this kind of vagary \Nwould really be enough to impress Herr Palfy.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.70,0:12:40.64,Default,,0,0,0,,A fine performance, \Nworthy of today's special concert. {/your play today was exceptionally good}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.64,0:12:42.31,Default,,0,0,0,,And it was so much like yours. {/similar}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.81,0:12:48.57,Default,,0,0,0,,They both are gifted in so many different ways...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.57,0:12:52.51,Default,,0,0,0,,They're the exact copy of you. \NKind at heart, but can stand their ground.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.85,0:12:57.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I like this mood.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.48,0:12:58.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's go.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.80,0:13:03.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, we'll go play somewhere now!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.76,0:13:05.30,Default,,0,0,0,,You two enjoy yourselves! {lit: as two, slowly}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.90,0:13:06.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait a minute!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.43,0:13:08.84,Default,,0,0,0,,We're off!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.54,0:13:13.61,Default,,0,0,0,,It's never easy with these girls...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.94,0:13:24.01,Default,,0,0,0,,How about we also take a stroll outside?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.81,0:13:27.91,Default,,0,0,0,,If possible, I would have liked to stay here for a bit.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.97,0:13:43.17,Default,,0,0,0,,I feel strangely sentimental here. {to get a lump in one's throat; to overflow with feelings; to be overwhelmed with emotion​}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.70,0:13:47.64,Default,,0,0,0,,This room brings back the times \Nwhen we lived together.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.37,0:13:51.04,Default,,0,0,0,,The room of a thousand memories. {/it's a room filled with many memories ...}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.58,0:13:59.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Seven years have passed, \Nand it's still the same.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.72,0:14:01.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Your place under the sun. {lit: smell of sunny spot; exposure to the sun - again, she uses smell in connection to the sun like before with luise's cheeks so I think it's intended so I tried to use similar wordings too}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.66,0:14:08.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Great!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.44,0:14:11.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Great, indeed! Dad and mom...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.13,0:14:12.88,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sure, they will...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.88,0:14:14.42,Default,,0,0,0,,They definitely will...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.42,0:14:15.44,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}reconcile! {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.44,0:14:18.15,Default,,0,0,0,,In just five days, it's fourteenth of October!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.15,0:14:20.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Our birthday!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.22,0:14:22.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's make it the best day ever!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.01,0:14:35.33,Default,,0,0,0,,She came with umbrellas...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.33,0:14:37.58,Default,,0,0,0,,For a joke, this is going too far.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.05,0:14:39.38,Default,,0,0,0,,I feel sorry for her.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.79,0:14:44.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Luise!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.72,0:14:48.86,Default,,0,0,0,,You were messing with me?! How dare... {/tricked/deceived}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.07,0:14:54.74,Default,,0,0,0,,We're sorry! Luise didn't do it out of bad intent.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.57,0:14:57.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Luise is now two...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.71,0:14:59.68,Default,,0,0,0,,What's the meaning of all this?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.14,0:15:02.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Luise and me are a pair of twins.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.38,0:15:04.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Twins?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.45,0:15:07.75,Default,,0,0,0,,How can this be...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.50,0:15:10.12,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm seeing a nightmare, am I?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.94,0:15:13.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Right now, we're happier than ever!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.51,0:15:17.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Both dad and mom \Nare closely by our side. {to surround; to encircle; to enclose; to fence; to wall in}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.17,0:15:38.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you still remember that time?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.42,0:15:41.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. I've not forgotten.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.03,0:15:45.75,Default,,0,0,0,,We used to sing a lot, in a duet. \NTo my piano accompaniment.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.58,0:15:50.22,Default,,0,0,0,,You were still a fameless composer, \Nblind to everything outside your dream. {/composer who didn't sell, only seeing your dream}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.80,0:15:56.21,Default,,0,0,0,,And you were determined and unyielding, not thinking twice \Nbefore quarreling with me over my egoism. {determined spirit; unyielding spirit; will and straight (ahead); direct; upright; erect​, saying I'm selfish, fought me immediately}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.21,0:15:59.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I even thought to myself, \N"How can one be so headstrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.80,0:16:01.16,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm flabbergasted..." {to be fascinated (by); to be captivated by; to be enchanted by; to gaze admiringly at; to watch in fascination}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.16,0:16:03.84,Default,,0,0,0,,But then, also, \N"Well, isn't it fascinating?" {charm; fascination; glamour; glamor; attraction; appeal}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.51,0:16:11.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Glad to see you've not changed a bit in that regard.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.93,0:16:13.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Even now, just as fascinating.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.89,0:16:18.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you really blame me for it, Herr "Busy-Busy"? {I think she means "you also/were the one who mistreated me/was wrongdoing, always saying "I work, work""}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.68,0:16:20.33,Default,,0,0,0,,I felt lonely.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.33,0:16:23.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Eventually, you wouldn't even give me \Nas much as a look.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.19,0:16:25.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Music was your only love.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.28,0:16:34.24,Default,,0,0,0,,One day, I felt like playing a little trick on you.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.47,0:16:39.87,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought, "if I tell him I'm leaving, \Nwould he probably look at me at least then?"
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.21,0:16:41.39,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you saying?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.39,0:16:42.88,Default,,0,0,0,,You did that to provoke me? {to try (out); to have a try (at); to test; to put to the test}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.60,0:16:44.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.92,0:16:48.65,Default,,0,0,0,,However, even then, \Nyou didn't make any attempt to stop me. {to detain; to check; to restrain; to stop}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.09,0:16:52.26,Default,,0,0,0,,But I... I thought you just \Ngrew cold to me, that's why...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.36,0:16:54.66,Default,,0,0,0,,But I never... {/I did?/my side/I'm the one?}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.38,0:16:58.23,Default,,0,0,0,,But it was you who acted \Nlike you no longer need me.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.63,0:17:01.20,Default,,0,0,0,,This is so complicated... {/how could you say that}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.47,0:17:04.20,Default,,0,0,0,,But it starts to clear up.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.20,0:17:08.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Could it be that we both fell victim \Nto a disastrous misunderstanding?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.24,0:17:22.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.55,0:17:25.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.19,0:17:29.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Orchestra tuning? {(musical) tuning}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.13,0:17:30.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Can't it wait just a bit? {/it's that time already}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.40,0:17:32.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Understood!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.69,0:17:35.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm needed elsewhere right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.89,0:17:38.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll have my leave, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.57,0:17:40.71,Default,,0,0,0,,No, wait please.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.10,0:17:45.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I still need to tell you something... \NEverything I couldn't say in the past years. {lit: I want discussion; talk; tête-à-tête; conference, until now, everything I didn't say...}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.20,0:17:46.87,Default,,0,0,0,,It's too late now, isn't it? {/already over}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.87,0:17:49.48,Default,,0,0,0,,This work won't take more than two hours.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.48,0:17:51.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Please wait for me in the Cafe Schubert.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.52,0:17:57.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Make sure to be there, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.74,0:18:03.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Cafe Schubert...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.16,0:18:07.67,Default,,0,0,0,,We two spent countless dates there.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.21,0:18:12.44,Default,,0,0,0,,We're home!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.93,0:18:14.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Welcome back, Frauleins.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.63,0:18:17.74,Default,,0,0,0,,I was talking to Frau Mistress on the phone just now.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.74,0:18:19.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Our mom called?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.51,0:18:25.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I think... She mentioned going to Cafe "Something," \Nso she's going to be a little late.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.28,0:18:27.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Cafe "Something?"
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.21,0:18:52.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Good, that settles it for today.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.78,0:18:58.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Herr Palfy.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.28,0:19:01.85,Default,,0,0,0,,We need to have a talk.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.35,0:19:04.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Frau Irene?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.46,0:19:53.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Just as father and mother seemed to be finally \Non their way to open their hearts to one another, {/gotten a little closer}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.60,0:19:57.90,Default,,0,0,0,,a major obstacle was about \Nto be wedged between them. {big obstacle; impediment; hindrance; barrier; difficulty was to lie in wait (for); to be on the watch (for); to wait (for); to watch (for)}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.37,0:20:04.91,Default,,0,0,0,,However, Lotte and Luise \Nare still altogether oblivious to what is coming to them.
Comment: 0,0:20:19.37,0:20:19.37,Sign,,0,0,0,,{chapter}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.31,0:20:28.84,Sign,,0,0,0,,A miserable romance {可哀想ね　ロマンス}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.84,0:20:32.30,Sign,,0,0,0,,A tear-jerking nuance {涙誘うニュアンス}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.30,0:20:36.02,Sign,,0,0,0,,If you turn another page of your memories, {想い出のページめくれば}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.02,0:20:38.93,Sign,,0,0,0,,Here she is - heroine of the past {追憶のヒロイン} {actually, "the heroine of the recollections" but that doesn't have a nice ring to it}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.15,0:20:50.57,Sign,,0,0,0,,I raise my eyes to your face - {あなたの面影　見上げて咲いている}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.57,0:20:54.33,Sign,,0,0,0,,Suddenly, I'm in full bloom {unsure, maybe "it's flourishing"}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.33,0:20:57.87,Sign,,0,0,0,,A sunflower amidst the blizzard - {act. in the middle of winter}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.87,0:21:01.27,Sign,,0,0,0,,that would be me, my dear {真冬のひまわり　それが私なの}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.71,0:21:04.44,Sign,,0,0,0,,Always on the verge of freezing, {凍えるような気持ちでいつも}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.29,0:21:07.84,Sign,,0,0,0,,My feelings are out of control -
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.84,0:21:12.39,Sign,,0,0,0,,Too stiff to even say "Do you still love me?" {「好き?」と尋くこともできず}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.39,0:21:16.54,Sign,,0,0,0,,My lips just keep wavering in this wind! {風に揺れていたわ}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.09,0:21:21.74,Sign,,0,0,0,,A pitiful Romance {いじらしいね　ロマンス}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.74,0:21:25.15,Sign,,0,0,0,,Something that only happens in dreams - {夢のような出来事}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.15,0:21:28.78,Sign,,0,0,0,,Trying hard to forget, I fell even more in love {忘れるために愛したの}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.78,0:21:31.55,Sign,,0,0,0,,with heroine of the past {追憶のヒロイン}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.60,0:21:36.37,Sign,,0,0,0,,Miracle that I came across now is hugging me tight {めぐりあえた奇跡　そっと抱きしめて}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.37,0:21:39.78,Sign,,0,0,0,,This is the story of my life, my duty is to protect it! {私だけの歴史　守ってゆくわ}
Comment: 0,0:21:43.37,0:21:43.37,Sign,,0,0,0,,{chapter}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.71,0:21:45.14,Sign,,0,0,0,,Next episode
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.45,0:21:49.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Luise, mom had disappeared!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.35,0:21:51.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Where did she go?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.45,0:21:53.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Last night, she didn't warn us.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.36,0:21:54.49,Default,,0,0,0,,This is strange!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.49,0:21:57.66,Sign,,0,0,0,,Could it be that something bad \Nhappened to her in Cafe Schubert?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.66,0:22:00.62,Sign,,0,0,0,,That must be dad's fault! \NDad offended her somehow!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.62,0:22:04.02,Sign,,0,0,0,,You think it's possible that mom \Nhad returned to Munich already?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.02,0:22:06.94,Sign,,0,0,0,,That's unacceptable! Totally unacceptable!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.94,0:22:09.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Next time, I and Myself:
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.24,0:22:11.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Saying Goodbyes? No!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.14,0:22:13.44,Sign,,0,0,0,,Episode 26 \N Saying Goodbyes? No! {サヨナラなんて、いや!}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.44,0:22:12.74,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Don't miss it!{\i0}
